{"repository": {"pullRequest": {"number": 974, "title": "set USER env var in entrypoint to support arbitrary container UIDs", "body": "`getpass.getuser()` in PyTorch's inductor cache init calls `pwd.getpwuid()` which fails with `KeyError` when the container runs with a UID that has no `/etc/passwd` entry (e.g. --user 955). Setting USER in the entrypoint makes `getpass.getuser()` return early from the env var without hitting pwd.", "baseRefName": "main", "baseRefOid": "751e7e7ed45d548e3e34adc5ac00ceefa18db164", "baseRepository": {"nameWithOwner": "h2oai/h2o-llmstudio"}, "url": "https://github.com/h2oai/h2o-llmstudio/pull/974", "createdAt": "2026-03-02T19:41:44Z", "mergedAt": "2026-03-04T11:45:55Z"}}, "base": {"repo": {"full_name": "h2oai/h2o-llmstudio"}, "sha": "751e7e7ed45d548e3e34adc5ac00ceefa18db164"}, "diff_url": "https://github.com/h2oai/h2o-llmstudio/pull/974.diff", "number": 974, "created_at": "2026-03-02T19:41:44Z", "merged_at": "2026-03-04T11:45:55Z", "resolved_issues": [967]}
{"repository": {"pullRequest": {"number": 980, "title": "fix(deps): [WIP] upgrade vulnerable dependencies (FedRAMP #979)", "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\n**WIP** \u2014 Upgrade Python and Go dependencies to resolve HIGH CVEs from FedRAMP vulnerability report.\r\n\r\n- **pyjwt** 2.11.0 \u2192 2.12.1 \u2014 fixes CVE-2026-32597 (HIGH)\r\n- **tornado** 6.5.4 \u2192 6.5.5 \u2014 fixes CVE-2026-31958 (HIGH), GHSA-78cv-mqj4-43f7 (MEDIUM)\r\n- **h2o-wave** 1.8.1 \u2192 1.8.2 \u2014 fixes Go stdlib CVEs in `waved` binary (CVE-2026-25679, CVE-2026-27142, CVE-2026-27139)\r\n- **wandb** 0.25.0 \u2192 0.25.1 \u2014 fixes same Go stdlib CVEs in `wandb-core` binary\r\n\r\n### Remaining vulnerabilities (all upstream, no fix available from us)\r\n\r\n| CVE | Severity | Package | Owner |\r\n|-----|----------|---------|-------|\r\n| CVE-2026-33186 | CRITICAL | grpc v1.79.2 in `wandb-core` | wandb (newly introduced, 30-day window) |\r\n| CVE-2025-69872 | MEDIUM | diskcache 5.6.3 | No upstream fix available |\r\n| CVE-2026-25537 | MEDIUM | jsonwebtoken in `uv`/`uvx` | astral-sh/uv |\r\n| CVE-2026-32766 | LOW | astral-tokio-tar in `uv`/`uvx` | astral-sh/uv |\r\n\r\nCloses https://github.com/h2oai/h2o-llmstudio/issues/979\r\n\r\n### EDIT 1\r\n\r\nThe CRITICAL is new (published after the initial FedRAMP scan). However, I'd wait a few days if wandb will release a fix.", "baseRefName": "main", "baseRefOid": "a4971c11ed2c93e531607670df7ae9cb673936b4", "baseRepository": {"nameWithOwner": "h2oai/h2o-llmstudio"}, "url": "https://github.com/h2oai/h2o-llmstudio/pull/980", "createdAt": "2026-03-17T14:06:48Z", "mergedAt": "2026-03-20T14:06:06Z"}}, "base": {"repo": {"full_name": "h2oai/h2o-llmstudio"}, "sha": "a4971c11ed2c93e531607670df7ae9cb673936b4"}, "diff_url": "https://github.com/h2oai/h2o-llmstudio/pull/980.diff", "number": 980, "created_at": "2026-03-17T14:06:48Z", "merged_at": "2026-03-20T14:06:06Z", "resolved_issues": [979]}
